DrPizza wrote:Yeah, early on the cleave is just horrible. It's bad if you're ranged, it's a fucking disaster if you're melee.From what I remember, it seems to have a fairly narrow cone. It goes pretty far forward, but if you're off to the side a bit you can avoid it. Unless the Kunkka is smart and purposely lines you up. It's really really hard to dodge it unless you're really far away if he's actively trying to hit you with it. But if he's just attackign the creep with it and not paying attention you can stand to the side usually.K0DE wrote:Had a great game on viper last night...that we lost. I got first blood, went back and forth ganking and killing my middle opponent (Zues). But we did not play as a team, people were KSing (or blaming each other, Magnataur was mad I "KS'ed" him with my normal attack) etc. I was doing great but we just did not mesh well. Was a pretty good game but would have been nice to have a little teamwork and for people to learn to focus the right people first (that being NOT Brewmaster...) and using their abilities - Alchemist was our "main" stun (I think so anyways, we had Lina and Mags as well but one has a delay and the other is an ult) and did not take UC until 12 or so.I am all about people playing their heroes the way they want but why you'd totally ignore one of the best stuns in the game in favor of a little more gold early on...arg. Sad thing is Alch is a decent PL counter but he went Moljinor instead of Radiance so we ended up getting overwhelmed with images.Heh, Magna getting pissed that a carry got a kill? Yep, sounds like bad teamwork... I know Magna can kind of be a carry as well, but come on, it's nice if Viper gets fed.And that Alch was probably using Dota2alttab.com. One of the dangers of rigidly following a build. Last I remember, they tell you to pick a lot of the gold levels early, because if you're good with alchemist, and you're not getting harassed too badly, you can bank a lot of money and get your radiance early. If you're not familiar with him though, it's better to go acid and stun. I think that's a poor build on dota2alttab personally. Because if a person is good with him, they'll already know to get the gold so they can rush radiance, but if they're not good at him and don't know his abilities (and consequently will be looking at a site for build info) then it's not a great idea.
