andyfatbastard wrote:Why the fuck do idiots run towards Roshan's spawn as soon as they see their opponents have killed him??? "Holy shit, our opponents are much stronger than they used to be, now's the perfect time to kill them because I know where one of them is!"Double-edged sword. If you do nothing about them getting Roshan, you're letting them do what they will with the 200 gold and you're letting them plan the encounter to use the Aegis. Sometimes you can catch 1-5 of them not at full health and not in the best position to fight that fight, and basically make them blow the gold on deaths and the aegis immediately, nullifying the Rosh kill.However that plan can easily backfire if you misplay it or force it from too far away, hence the double-edgedness andyfatbastard
